resources.string: Would you like to participate in setting up one of our festivals? Would you like to help our team in some way? Click on this button to become a volunteer!

Un-Mute, it\'s the non-profit organization that finds you the little nuggets of the Belgian scene! The objective is simple: to make the local independent scene accessible to the public, thanks to the crowdfunding system applied to the world of festivals.

" Electro-pop style artist from Liège. Self-taught musician. In the oven and in the mill, he writes, performs and composes songs in the English language, but also in Spanish, and more occasionally in French."
The artists work together to fill the festival hall, united behind a common goal: the minimum number of tickets to validate the event.
You don\'t always have to look very far to find talent... Near you, in your region, emerging artists are just waiting to be heard.
Le festival est produit sur base du financement collectif. Acheter un ticket revient à participer directement à la production de l\'événement !
Does your playlist always feature the same artists? But there\'s no shortage of variety. We\'ve found the nuggets for tomorrow!
At the oven and the mill, he writes, interprets and composes songs in English, but also in Spanish and, more occasionally, in French.
Artist from Liège with an electro-pop style.

The Vectors is a rock band formed in 2015 following in the footsteps of English bands such as Arctic Monkeys or Muse with inspiration from muscular American bands such as Rage Against the Machine or Queens of the Stone Age.

A post rock trio composed of bass, guitar and drums. Yakhchal creates instrumental songs made of melancholic atmospheres and melodies, repetitive psychedelic loops and effects that evolve into explosive riffs.
